attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 4th Edition
text: A domesticated carnivorous mammal (Canis familiaris) related to the foxes and wolves and raised in a wide variety of breeds.

attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 4th Edition
text: Any of various carnivorous mammals of the family Canidae, such as the dingo.

attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 4th Edition
text: A male animal of the family Canidae, especially of the fox or a domesticated breed.
